343
00:22:57,332 --> 00:22:58,482
This is dumb.

344
00:23:00,755 --> 00:23:02,005
So how are you?

345
00:23:03,675 --> 00:23:04,880
When did you move in?

346
00:23:07,575 --> 00:23:08,575
Last week.

347
00:23:09,275 --> 00:23:11,425
And how has it been going so far?

348
00:23:13,935 --> 00:23:14,890
Okay, I guess.

349
00:23:15,265 --> 00:23:16,715
Where's your house?

350
00:23:16,985 --> 00:23:18,685
In the middle of nowhere.

351
00:23:19,105 --> 00:23:20,705
Do you like your room?

352
00:23:20,935 --> 00:23:21,985
Not really.

353
00:23:22,335 --> 00:23:24,365
In Brooklyn,
my room is painted blue.

354
00:23:24,490 --> 00:23:26,610
What if you and your mom
go to the hardware store

355
00:23:26,778 --> 00:23:28,478
and buy some blue paint?

356
00:23:29,385 --> 00:23:30,935
That way your room...

357
00:23:31,715 --> 00:23:34,400
your room can look the same
as it did in Brooklyn.

358
00:23:34,525 --> 00:23:35,525
I guess.

359
00:23:36,165 --> 00:23:38,920
How are you and your mom
getting on these days?

360
00:23:39,045 --> 00:23:40,445
She's really busy.

361
00:23:41,105 --> 00:23:44,502
She's teaching a lot,
so I don't get to see her very much.

362
00:23:44,785 --> 00:23:47,535
But you have dinner together
every night, yeah?

363
00:23:48,455 --> 00:23:50,355
And then you tell her...

364
00:23:50,895 --> 00:23:52,469
You tell her all about your day.

365
00:23:55,795 --> 00:23:57,995
Has your dad come up to visit you?

366
00:23:58,555 --> 00:23:59,805
Not yet, but...

367
00:24:00,210 --> 00:24:02,780
This weekend he's coming to get me
and we're going to the city.

368
00:24:02,905 --> 00:24:03,905
Cool.

369
00:24:04,485 --> 00:24:06,608
But I'm not sure
what we're gonna do there.

370
00:24:06,776 --> 00:24:08,326
When you talk to him,

371
00:24:09,965 --> 00:24:13,580
maybe you could just make a list
of the things that you want to do.

372
00:24:13,705 --> 00:24:16,493
Maybe, I don't know,
go to a basketball game,

373
00:24:16,685 --> 00:24:20,385
maybe even go back to that restaurant
where you had the paella.

374
00:24:21,715 --> 00:24:22,791
That'd be fun.

375
00:24:23,777 --> 00:24:25,377
So how are things going at school?

376
00:24:27,105 --> 00:24:28,672
All the kids are strange.

377
00:24:28,840 --> 00:24:30,140
I bet there's...

378
00:24:30,535 --> 00:24:33,051
one or two kids
that you kind of like.

379
00:24:37,115 --> 00:24:39,215
It's gonna take a while, Oliver.

380
00:24:40,495 --> 00:24:43,445
Everything's gonna be
new and strange for a bit.

381
00:24:44,395 --> 00:24:46,545
But I think you're gonna do okay.

382
00:24:47,775 --> 00:24:51,675
I think things are gonna work out
